1951;;Teresa;;American;;Fred Zinnemann;;Pier Angeli, John Ericson, Peggy Ann Garner;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teresa_(film);;Phillip Cass, a sensitive, young man (John Ericson), is saddled with a mother from hell. While fighting in Italy during World War II, he marries a sweet, young Italian woman (Pier Angeli) who might be able to change his life and satisfy his desire to be loved. Readjustment proves difficult as the young couple have to share a New York apartment with his parents and sister, while Philip feels a failure at menial jobs. The birth of a baby finally gives the couple new hope.